ENTRY       EC 4.2.1.127                Enzyme
NAME        linalool dehydratase;
            linalool hydro-lyase (myrcene-forming)
CLASS       Lyases;
            Carbon-oxygen lyases;
            Hydro-lyases
SYSNAME     (3S)-linalool hydro-lyase (myrcene-forming)
REACTION    (3S)-linalool = myrcene + H2O [RN:R09702]
ALL_REAC    R09702
SUBSTRATE   (3S)-linalool [CPD:C11389]
PRODUCT     myrcene [CPD:C06074];
            H2O [CPD:C00001]
COMMENT     In absence of oxygen the bifunctional linalool dehydratase-isomerase can catalyse in vitro two reactions, the hydration of myrcene to (3S)-linalool and the isomerization of (3S)-linalool to geraniol, the latter activity being classified as EC 5.4.4.4, geraniol isomerase.
